WEBVTT

00:00.523 --> 00:03.983
♪ It seems today
that all you see ♪

00:04.019 --> 00:07.253
♪ Is violence in movies
and sex on TV ♪

00:07.289 --> 00:10.857
♪ But where are those
good old-fashioned values ♪

00:10.893 --> 00:13.860
♪ On which we used to rely? ♪

00:13.896 --> 00:17.363
♪ Lucky there's a family guy ♪

00:17.399 --> 00:20.766
♪ Lucky there's a man
who positively can do ♪

00:20.802 --> 00:22.201
♪ All the things that make us ♪

00:22.237 --> 00:23.603
♪ Laugh and cry ♪

00:23.639 --> 00:29.246
♪ He's... a...
Fam... ily... Guy! ♪

00:29.282 --> 00:30.435
Subtitles by explosiveskull

00:30.471 --> 00:31.945
Hi there. It's me, Peter.

00:31.981 --> 00:34.714
You know, when it comes
to making dreams come alive,

00:34.750 --> 00:37.016
there used to be nothing
like the movies.

00:37.052 --> 00:38.451
So we thought it would
be fun to ask

00:38.487 --> 00:41.854
a few visionary Hollywood
directors to create his...

00:41.890 --> 00:43.290
let's be honest, his...

00:43.326 --> 00:46.359
own unique version of
the same Family Guy story:

00:46.395 --> 00:48.027
"Peter Gets Fired."

00:48.063 --> 00:50.096
Of the countless
directors we contacted,

00:50.132 --> 00:52.364
three did not
say no immediately,

00:52.400 --> 00:54.867
and I got a weird message
from Paul Verhoeven

00:54.903 --> 00:56.802
that I could not understand.

00:56.838 --> 00:58.704
Ah, Pieoter,
habinsky Vermhoeven.

00:58.740 --> 01:00.706
Kibbensme comfurdle. Stupf.

01:00.742 --> 01:02.575
I've listened to that
over a hundred times now.

01:02.611 --> 01:03.810
I-I got nothin'.

01:03.846 --> 01:05.212
Anyway,
here's our first director,

01:05.248 --> 01:07.247
Quentin Tarantino.

01:10.519 --> 01:12.718
♪ Hey, well,
I'm the friendly stranger ♪

01:12.754 --> 01:16.223
♪ In the black sedan, won't you
hop inside my car? ♪

01:16.259 --> 01:18.592
♪ I got pictures, got candy,
I'm a lovable man ♪

01:18.628 --> 01:20.593
