01:30.506 --> 01:31.837
- ♪ That I love ya ♪
- ♪ Love ya ♪

01:31.873 --> 01:33.239
- ♪ I need ya ♪
- ♪ Need ya ♪

01:33.275 --> 01:36.242
♪ I want you,
got to have you, child ♪

01:36.278 --> 01:39.646
♪ Great God in heaven,
you know I love you... ♪

01:39.682 --> 01:41.647
- What's in your lunch?
- Pizza.

01:41.683 --> 01:43.082
From home or from a place?

01:43.118 --> 01:44.120
A place.

01:46.121 --> 01:49.256
♪ Well, if you wants to be
a movie star ♪

01:49.292 --> 01:51.828
♪ I'll get a ticket
to Hollywood. ♪

01:54.563 --> 01:57.364
Griffin, you're
three hours late.

01:57.400 --> 02:00.099
Stop trying to be a clock,
you ain't got the face for it.

02:00.135 --> 02:02.102
I've had enough
of your nonsense.

02:02.138 --> 02:05.639
Here's Christoph Waltz
to fire you in a weird accent.

02:05.675 --> 02:08.844
Yer fi-YERD!

02:22.057 --> 02:23.425
It's a cliché.

02:25.860 --> 02:27.294
You think you can fire me?

02:27.330 --> 02:30.462
I'm taking this keg as payback.

02:34.870 --> 02:37.674
Cinema is an event.

02:59.628 --> 03:02.798
- Where's my family?
- Dead. All of them.

03:20.483 --> 03:22.115
Oh, my God, where am I?

03:22.151 --> 03:24.417
- What happened?
- Ugh! Coma breath.

03:24.453 --> 03:26.385
Coma?!
How long was I out?

03:26.421 --> 03:28.187
- What year is this?
- It's whatever year

03:28.223 --> 03:30.289
Quentin Tarantino used
to watch television.

03:30.325 --> 03:31.758
Well, can I go home?

03:31.794 --> 03:32.925
Well, you're not
really ready,

03:32.961 --> 03:34.060
but if it's for revenge,

03:34.096 --> 03:35.527
you can stab me
with this scalpel

03:35.563 --> 03:37.229
- and then run out.
- Thanks.

03:37.265 --> 03:39.699
Oh, that was
unnecessary but cool.

03:39.735 --> 03:41.571
So awesome!

03:55.318 --> 03:56.920
